            <abstract xml:lang="fr">
              <p>We consider the problem of estimating the mean absorp-tion coefficients of a room from an impulse response us-ing  supervised  learning  on  simulated  training  sets.   Twoneural network architectures and two training dataset de-signs are considered.  The proposed approach is shown toyield  smaller  estimation  errors  than  the  classical  Sabineand Eyring formulas, despite not relying on any geomet-rical information on the room.  Simulated results demon-strate the robustness of the approach under different chal-lenging acoustic conditions.</p>
